# Credentials. srs-to-jira reads JIRA_PAT from the environment and its SKILL.md shows
# a shell block — which is exactly how a token ends up in a committed .env.
.env
.env.*

# srs-to-jira workspace: jira-map.json carries the internal Jira hostname and
# tasks.json carries the whole SRS. The skill also drops a `*` .gitignore in here on
# first run, so it stays private inside a customer's repo too.
morkit/output/jira/

